00:04:54.590 --> 00:05:02.140
So I'll call this
N of A, this line.

00:05:02.140 --> 00:05:05.400
Well, you see I'm trying to
draw a three dimensional space.

00:05:05.400 --> 00:05:07.720
That line goes both ways.

00:05:07.720 --> 00:05:09.560
But it's perpendicular
to the plane.

00:05:09.560 --> 00:05:11.570
That's the fabulous part.

00:05:11.570 --> 00:05:13.070
That's wonderful.

00:05:13.070 --> 00:05:17.640
This line, the null space, is
perpendicular to this plane,

00:05:17.640 --> 00:05:20.140
the row space.

00:05:20.140 --> 00:05:21.150
You want to know why?

00:05:21.150 --> 00:05:22.840
You want to just see it?

00:05:22.840 --> 00:05:27.460
Because if I take A
times v, that would be 1,

00:05:27.460 --> 00:05:32.570
2, 3 times v. 1, 2, 3 is
perpendicular to that.

00:05:32.570 --> 00:05:35.560
How do I check perpendicular
for two vectors?

00:05:35.560 --> 00:05:37.750
1, 2, 3 dot product.

00:05:37.750 --> 00:05:42.760
1, minus 2, 1, the dot product
is 1 times 1, minus 2 times

00:05:42.760 --> 00:05:46.910
2-- that's 4-- plus
3 times 1, that's 3.

00:05:46.910 --> 00:05:49.970
1 minus 4 plus 3 is 0.

00:05:49.970 --> 00:05:54.120
And, similarly, 4
minus 10 plus 6 is 0.

00:05:54.120 --> 00:05:57.760
So this is a right angle here.

00:05:57.760 --> 00:06:03.320
It's a right angle, 90 degrees
between those two subspaces.

00:06:03.320 --> 00:06:07.090
And again, in this
example, one space

00:06:07.090 --> 00:06:09.740
