00:09:32.840 --> 00:09:36.440
I like having just column
space and null space.

00:09:36.440 --> 00:09:42.000
So I-- and I'm OK to
go to A transpose.

00:09:42.000 --> 00:09:44.770
Now, what's that fourth guy?

00:09:44.770 --> 00:09:49.080
Oh, just by beautifulness,
general principles of elegance

00:09:49.080 --> 00:09:49.710
here.

00:09:49.710 --> 00:09:52.950
If I have columns space
and null space of A,

00:09:52.950 --> 00:09:55.440
and if I have column
space of A transpose,

00:09:55.440 --> 00:10:01.940
the fourth guy has to be the
null space of A transpose.

00:10:01.940 --> 00:10:05.510
Sorry, I wrote that
so small, so small.

00:10:05.510 --> 00:10:07.550
But I did write this
a little larger.

00:10:07.550 --> 00:10:11.400
The null space of A
transpose, all the w's

00:10:11.400 --> 00:10:13.620
that solve that equation.

00:10:13.620 --> 00:10:15.490
A transpose w equals 0.

00:10:15.490 --> 00:10:19.130
The null space of A
transpose is all the w's that

00:10:19.130 --> 00:10:21.370
solve that equation.

00:10:21.370 --> 00:10:23.610
What does that
equation looks like?

00:10:23.610 --> 00:10:24.160
Ha!

00:10:24.160 --> 00:10:29.850
Well, that equation--
A transpose

00:10:29.850 --> 00:10:31.850
will have two columns.

00:10:31.850 --> 00:10:36.450
So A transpose-- this will
be w1 of the first column.

00:10:36.450 --> 00:10:41.450
1, 2, 3, when I transpose.

00:10:41.450 --> 00:10:50.560
And w2 of the second column,
