00:10:54.820 --> 00:10:59.180
Well, now I've got, for this
null space-- because my matrix

00:10:59.180 --> 00:11:05.140
here is 2 by 3, for
this fourth subspace,

00:11:05.140 --> 00:11:10.700
I have three equations and
only two unknowns, w1 and w2.

00:11:10.700 --> 00:11:13.620
And, in fact, the
only solutions are

00:11:13.620 --> 00:11:19.080
w1 equals 0, w2 equals
0, because that's

00:11:19.080 --> 00:11:21.810
the only way I can get
combination-- that's

00:11:21.810 --> 00:11:24.300
the only combination
of that vector

00:11:24.300 --> 00:11:29.300
and that vector that gives
me 0 is to take 0 of that

00:11:29.300 --> 00:11:30.926
and zero of that.

00:11:30.926 --> 00:11:36.780
Do you see that the-- in
this example, the null space

00:11:36.780 --> 00:11:42.930
of A transpose is just--
null space of A transpose--

00:11:42.930 --> 00:11:48.710
is just what I call
the 0 subspace.

00:11:48.710 --> 00:11:51.920
The subspace that has
only one puny vector

00:11:51.920 --> 00:11:53.680
in it, the 0 vector.

00:11:53.680 --> 00:11:54.730
But that's OK.

00:11:54.730 --> 00:11:57.370
It follows the
rule for subspaces.

00:11:57.370 --> 00:12:01.640
And it completes the
picture of four subspaces.

00:12:01.640 --> 00:12:10.560
In other examples, we could
have all four subspaces nonzero.

00:12:10.560 --> 00:12:17.360
But we would have two over
here that, together, complete

00:12:17.360 --> 00:12:19.880
the full N dimensional space.

00:12:19.880 --> 00:12:24.760
And over here, we have two that
together complete the full M

00:12:24.760 --> 00:12:26.220
dimensional space.

00:12:26.220 --> 00:12:31.960
And here, for this matrix, M was
2, so that this is completed.

00:12:31.960 --> 00:12:38.910
The column space was
all of R2 in this case.

00:12:38.910 --> 00:12:41.990
All of two dimensional
space was the column space,

00:12:41.990 --> 00:12:45.340
and that didn't leave any
room for the left null space,

00:12:45.340 --> 00:12:47.350
the null space of A transpose.

00:12:47.350 --> 00:12:49.370
So do you see that picture?

00:12:49.370 --> 00:12:54.380
Let we may be just sketch it
once more with a clean board.

00:12:54.380 --> 00:12:57.360
So I have the row space.

00:12:57.360 --> 00:13:02.560
Let me draw it maybe going
