00:13:58.250 --> 00:14:02.260
So this row space, in that
example, was two dimensional.

00:14:02.260 --> 00:14:03.440
It was a plane.

00:14:03.440 --> 00:14:08.310
In general, the
dimension equals--

00:14:08.310 --> 00:14:15.480
let's say R. That's an important
number, the rank of A. Oh,

00:14:15.480 --> 00:14:17.280
that's a key number.

00:14:17.280 --> 00:14:21.880
Maybe, I better speak separately
about the rank of a matrix.

00:14:21.880 --> 00:14:25.290
But I'll complete the idea here.

00:14:25.290 --> 00:14:29.560
So the dimension
of the row space

00:14:29.560 --> 00:14:32.230
is the number of
independent rows.

00:14:32.230 --> 00:14:35.440
And I call that number
R. And the beauty

00:14:35.440 --> 00:14:38.410
is that this has
the same dimension.

00:14:38.410 --> 00:14:44.410
Dimension Is also
the rank R. Can

00:14:44.410 --> 00:14:47.660
I say that wonderful
fact in a sentence?

00:14:47.660 --> 00:14:53.150
The column space and the row
space have the same dimension.

00:14:53.150 --> 00:14:56.490
The number of independent
rows equals the number

00:14:56.490 --> 00:14:58.200
of independent columns.

00:14:58.200 --> 00:15:06.740
That's like a miracle for a
giant matrix, say 57 by 212,

00:15:06.740 --> 00:15:09.290
there might be 40
independent rows.

00:15:09.290 --> 00:15:11.880
Then, there would be
40 independent columns.

00:15:11.880 --> 00:15:15.950
And then the null space
and the left null space

00:15:15.950 --> 00:15:17.940
have the remaining dimension.

00:15:17.940 --> 00:15:26.600
So the null space has dimension
N minus R because, altogether--

00:15:26.600 --> 00:15:28.730
together they have dimension N.

00:15:28.730 --> 00:15:35.540
And this has dimension M minus
R because, together, they

00:15:35.540 --> 00:15:41.560
have dimension M. That's the
picture with the dimensions put

00:15:41.560 --> 00:15:42.220
in.

00:15:42.220 --> 00:15:49.540
And let me say a little more
about the idea of dimension

